* ===========================================================================
* MCC_BUILD_X64_LMDB.DTS
* Build CDX index containers and tags for the x64 MCC tables, then build the
* LMDB backing store from those CDX containers.
*
* Status:  CANDIDATE / REVIEW_BEFORE_EXECUTION
* Safety:  MUTATING
* Purpose: Produce indexes/x64/*.cdx (PUBLISHED) and the LMDB backing store
*          under lmdb/x64/*.cdx.d (DERIVED - NEVER PUBLISHED).
* Inputs:  dottalkpp/data/dbf/x64/*.DBF   (from mcc_build_x64.dts)
* Outputs: dottalkpp/data/indexes/x64/*.cdx     <- commit these
*          dottalkpp/data/lmdb/x64/*.cdx.d/     <- gitignored, 53 GB class
* Mutation: CDX containers, lmdb-index-backend, filesystem, order-state
* Fixture: regenerable from dbf/x64 + this script
* Gate:    maintainer authorization required
*
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* CORRECTED 2026-07-14 -- the first draft of this script was wrong.
*
* It used  INDEX ON <field> TAG <name>  to build CDX tags, and  SETLMDB  to
* "materialize" the LMDB env. Both were wrong:
*
*   INDEX ON   builds an INX file, not a CDX tag.
*              (DOTTALKPP_COMMAND_REFERENCE_GUIDE_V1.md: "Build an INX index
*              file from the current table using a field key")
*   SETLMDB    only SELECTS LMDB-backed ordering for an already-built env.
*              (cmd_setlmdb.cpp: "select LMDB-backed ordering per area")
*   BUILDLMDB  is the builder.
*              (cmd_buildlmdb.cpp: "BUILDLMDB for CDX containers -> LMDB
*              backing store", "data\indexes\students.cdx -> data\lmdb\
*              students.cdx.d")
*
* The proven pipeline, per 154 occurrences of "BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES" across the
* .dts corpus and the canonical script
* dottalkpp/data/scripts/comments/SOURCE_COMMENT_IMPORT_ONLY.dts:
*
*     SET PATH DBF / INDEXES / LMDB
*     SELECT <n>
*     USE <table>
*     CDX CREATE
*     CDX ADDTAG <field>
*     BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
*
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* RESOLVED DRIFT: expression indexes are NOT a DotTalk++ capability.
*
* dbf/x64/community_college_x64_schema.txt suggests composite keys:
*     STUDENTS:  INDEX ON UPPER(LNAME+FNAME) TAG NAME
*     CLASSES:   INDEX ON TERM+CID+STR(SEC,2) TAG TCSEC
*
* Three independent sources say otherwise:
*   1. src/cli/cmd_index.cpp usage block:      INDEX ON <field> TAG <name>
*   2. DOTTALKPP_COMMAND_REFERENCE_GUIDE_V1:   "using a field key"
*   3. Every INDEX ON in the entire .dts corpus (40+ statements): bare fields.
*      Zero expressions. Not one UPPER(), not one concatenation.
*
* The schema file says "create in FoxPro". It is FoxPro advice that was never
* DotTalk++ practice. Composite tags NAME and TCSEC are therefore NOT built.
* Single-field tags only, below.
*
*   DOTSCRIPT TRACE scripts\mcc\mcc_build_x64_lmdb.dts OUT tmp\mcc_x64_lmdb.log
* ===========================================================================

SET ECHO OFF

ECHO ========================================================
ECHO MCC x64 -- CDX containers + LMDB backing store
ECHO CDX  -> indexes/x64/*.cdx      (PUBLISHED)
ECHO LMDB -> lmdb/x64/*.cdx.d       (DERIVED, gitignored)
ECHO ========================================================

* --- Bootstrap state explicitly (Readiness Seed 3) --------------------------
* Do NOT use "DO X64" here. The DOTSCRIPT resolver resolves relative to the
* INVOKING SCRIPT'S directory (scripts/mcc/), not the data root -- it would
* look for scripts/mcc/X64.dts, miss, REPORT the miss, and CONTINUE with the
* path slots unchanged. That exact failure hit mcc_build_x32.dts on
* 2026-07-14: PATH DBF stayed on DBF/og, so the script indexed the ORIGINALS
* and wrote 11 stray .cnx files into indexes/ root.
*
* The profile is three lines. Inline them. Each .dts sets its own environment.

WORKSPACE CLOSE
SET PATH DBF DBF/x64
SET PATH INDEXES INDEXES/x64
SET PATH LMDB LMDB/x64
ECHO [SETUP] DBF -> DBF/x64   INDEXES -> INDEXES/x64   LMDB -> LMDB/x64

* ===========================================================================
* One table per block: open, create container, add tags, build LMDB.
* BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES archives any existing env first, then rebuilds without
* the destructive prompt path. CLEAN and YES are both required for a
* non-interactive rebuild (cmd_buildlmdb.cpp workflow policy).
* ===========================================================================

* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* TAG SET -- harvested from the live x32 containers on 2026-07-14 and confirmed
* by the maintainer as identical for x64. NOT taken from the schema notes.
*
* The x32 run proved the schema notes UNDER-DESCRIBE the real indexes. Every
* CNX CREATE reported "file already exists" and every CNX ADDTAG reported "tag
* already exists", so REINDEX rebuilt tags the script had never declared:
*
*     STUDENTS   notes: SID          actual: SID MAJOR LNAME FNAME DOB GPA
*     CLASSES    notes: CLS_ID       actual: CLS_ID TERM CID ROOM TID
*     TEACHERS   notes: TID DEPT_ID  actual: TID DEPT_ID LNAME FNAME
*     ROOMS      notes: ROOM         actual: ROOM BLDG
*     MAJORS     notes: MAJOR        actual: MAJOR DEPT_ID
*     STUD_MAJ   notes: SID          actual: SID MAJOR
*     TASSIGN    notes: CLS_ID       actual: CLS_ID TID
*     BUILDING   notes: (none)       actual: BLDG
*
* A build script that only appears to work because the containers already exist
* is not a rebuild lane. Declaring the real set makes this reproducible from an
* EMPTY indexes/x64 directory.
*
* Authority: live containers + maintainer confirmation. Not the schema prose.
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

ECHO --- BUILDING ---
SELECT 0
USE BUILDING
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG BLDG
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- STUDENTS ---
SELECT 1
USE STUDENTS
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG SID
CDX ADDTAG MAJOR
CDX ADDTAG LNAME
CDX ADDTAG FNAME
CDX ADDTAG DOB
CDX ADDTAG GPA
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- TEACHERS ---
SELECT 2
USE TEACHERS
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG TID
CDX ADDTAG DEPT_ID
CDX ADDTAG LNAME
CDX ADDTAG FNAME
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- COURSES ---
SELECT 3
USE COURSES
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG CID
CDX ADDTAG DEPT_ID
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- CLASSES ---
SELECT 4
USE CLASSES
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG CLS_ID
CDX ADDTAG TERM
CDX ADDTAG CID
CDX ADDTAG ROOM
CDX ADDTAG TID
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- ENROLL ---
SELECT 5
USE ENROLL
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG SID
CDX ADDTAG CLS_ID
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- ROOMS ---
SELECT 6
USE ROOMS
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG ROOM
CDX ADDTAG BLDG
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- MAJORS ---
SELECT 7
USE MAJORS
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG MAJOR
CDX ADDTAG DEPT_ID
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- DEPT ---
SELECT 8
USE DEPT
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG DEPT_ID
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- TERMS ---
SELECT 9
USE TERMS
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG TERM
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- STUD_MAJ ---
SELECT 10
USE STUD_MAJ
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG SID
CDX ADDTAG MAJOR
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- TASSIGN ---
SELECT 11
USE TASSIGN
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG CLS_ID
CDX ADDTAG TID
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
CDX TAGS

* ===========================================================================
* PROOF -- logical order, not file existence
* ===========================================================================
* Proving a .cdx file EXISTS is not proof the index orders records correctly.
* Open the set, attach, select the tag, and read the records back in order.
* SMARTLIST rather than LIST, because logical order is the behavior under test
* (AI_BABY_BOOTSTRAP_CARD: "Use SMARTLIST rather than LIST for order/index
* testing unless LIST itself is the target").
*
* USE auto-attaches flavor-appropriate indexes -- x64/v128 prefer CDX -- so an
* explicit SET INDEX should not be needed after the containers exist. It is
* issued anyway so the transcript shows the attach explicitly rather than
* relying on an implicit one.

ECHO ========================================================
ECHO PROOF -- open the set, read back in logical order
ECHO ========================================================

WORKSPACE CLOSE
SET PATH DBF DBF/x64
SET PATH INDEXES INDEXES/x64
SET PATH LMDB LMDB/x64
WORKSPACE OPEN DBF
WORKSPACE

ECHO Areas must be under dbf\x64 -- NOT dbf\og. If they are under og,
ECHO the path slots did not switch and everything above is invalid.

ECHO --- STUDENTS under CDX tag order ---
SELECT STUDENTS
SET INDEX TO STUDENTS
SET ORDER TO TAG SID
TOP
SMARTLIST SID,LNAME,FNAME NEXT 10

ECHO --- STUDENTS under LMDB-backed ordering (same tag, same order expected) ---
SETLMDB STUDENTS SID
TOP
SMARTLIST SID,LNAME,FNAME NEXT 10

* SETLMDB 0 clears ordering (physical). NOT "SETLMDB PHYSICAL" -- that form
* does not exist. The 2026-07-14 run proved it: SETLMDB PHYSICAL treated
* PHYSICAL as a container name and failed with
*     "openCdx: LMDB env missing: ...\PHYSICAL.cdx.d"
* Per SET LMDB USAGE: "SET LMDB 0 clears ordering and closes the current
* index manager."
*
* NOTE: mcc_exhaustive_full_regression_canaries_lmdb.dts uses SETLMDB PHYSICAL
* in several places. It is failing there too, silently. Worth a look.

SETLMDB 0

ECHO --- ENROLL under CDX tag order ---
SELECT ENROLL
SET INDEX TO ENROLL
SET ORDER TO TAG SID
TOP
SMARTLIST SID,CLS_ID NEXT 10

* ===========================================================================
* SAVE THE WORKSPACE
* ===========================================================================
* WORKSPACE SAVE persists the open areas plus the relations graph (if one
* exists), indexes, and tags. That makes the whole fixture set reopenable in
* one step instead of twelve, and captures the index/tag state we just built.

ECHO ========================================================
ECHO SAVE -- persist areas + relations + indexes + tags
ECHO ========================================================

WORKSPACE SAVE mcc_x64

ECHO ========================================================
ECHO MCC x64 index build complete.
ECHO
ECHO REVIEW THE FULL TRANSCRIPT. A zero exit code is NOT proof --
ECHO the DotScript runner reports unknown commands and continues.
ECHO
ECHO Reject or investigate:
ECHO   - Unknown command
ECHO   - CDX CREATE refusing an existing container (it will NOT overwrite;
ECHO     on a rebuild over an existing set this is expected, not an error --
ECHO     but confirm the existing tags are the ones you want)
ECHO   - missing table, field, or tag errors
ECHO   - BUILDLMDB prompting instead of proceeding (CLEAN YES should prevent)
ECHO   - SMARTLIST output NOT in logical tag order
ECHO   - CDX and LMDB orderings DISAGREEING for the same tag
ECHO   - known canary: ROOMS has failed SETLMDB in past runs
ECHO     (see mcc_exhaustive_full_regression_canaries_lmdb.dts)
ECHO
ECHO Commit:  indexes/x64/*.cdx
ECHO Ignore:  lmdb/x64/*.cdx.d/   (rebuild with this script)
ECHO
ECHO Default BUILDLMDB mapsize is 128 MiB (MEDIUM). The MCC tables are small
ECHO (84 KB total), so no preset override is used. If a table ever outgrows
ECHO the map, use BUILDLMDB CLEAN MAPSIZE <n> YES.
ECHO ========================================================
